de.bpmnaftool.model.aristaflow.graph.node
Interface Node

All Known Implementing Classes:
AndJoinNode, AndSplitNode, EndFlowNode, EndLoopNode, NodeImpl, NormalNode, StartFlowNode, StartLoopNode, XorJoinNode, XorSplitNode
public interface Node

Abstract representation of a node. Instead of using this generalized node, the specialized sub-types should be used. The purpose of this interface is to define methods which are needed for all types of nodes. It is not possible to create an instance of this class (protected constructor) - use the subclasses instead.

Author:
Felix Härer

getCorrepondingBlockNode

Node getCorrepondingBlockNode()
Returns the corresponding block node of this node. A block consists of a split and a join Node, e.g. xor split and xor join. The corresponding block node for a split node is the join node and vice versa.

Returns:
corresponding block node

setCorrespondingBlockNode

void setCorrespondingBlockNode(Node node)

Parameters:
node - corresponding block node
